      pearl: "First-line for uncomplicated Candida albicans infections; excellent bioavailability (oral = IV); used for step-down from echinocandin in stable candidemia; C. krusei is intrinsically resistant and C. glabrata has dose-dependent susceptibility—use echinocandin instead"
