    pearls: ["The ADA/APA consensus monitoring schedule: weight monthly x3 then quarterly; fasting glucose and lipids at baseline, 12 weeks, then annually (glucose) or every 5 years (lipids); waist circumference and BP at baseline then annually","A weight gain of >7% from baseline is the FDA-defined threshold for clinically significant weight gain and should trigger intervention (agent switch, metformin, or intensified lifestyle measures)","Clozapine and olanzapine carry the highest metabolic risk; aripiprazole, ziprasidone, and lurasidone are considered metabolically neutral—consider these for patients with metabolic risk factors","Metabolic monitoring is frequently underperformed in clinical practice—studies show only 25-30% of patients on SGAs receive guideline-concordant metabolic screening; this represents a major patient safety gap","Diabetic ketoacidosis has been reported with SGAs (especially olanzapine and clozapine) sometimes without prior documented hyperglycemia—educate patients to report polyuria, polydipsia, and rapid weight loss immediately","AIMS assessment is separate from metabolic monitoring but equally critical: perform at baseline, every 6 months for SGAs, every 3 months for FGAs; tardive dyskinesia risk increases with duration of treatment and cumulative dose"],
