        options: ["Administer benztropine 1-2 mg IM or diphenhydramine 50 mg IM","Increase haloperidol dose to achieve better symptom control","Administer lorazepam for anxiety-related muscle tension","Obtain a CT scan of the cervical spine"],
        correct: 0,
        rationale: "Acute dystonia (torticollis) is caused by dopamine-acetylcholine imbalance from D2 blockade in the nigrostriatal pathway. Treatment is anticholinergic agents: benztropine 1-2 mg IM/IV or diphenhydramine 50 mg IM/IV for immediate relief. This is a medication side effect, not a structural problem requiring imaging."
