      name: "Magnesium Sulfate",
      type: "Electrolyte replacement / antiarrhythmic",
      action: "First-line treatment for torsades de pointes regardless of serum magnesium level; stabilizes cardiac membrane by modulating calcium and potassium channel activity, suppresses early afterdepolarizations that trigger TdP, and shortens the action potential duration; also required for cellular potassium repletion (hypokalemia is refractory to correction without adequate magnesium)",
