    management: ["Initiate antipsychotic at low dose and titrate gradually to minimize side effects ('start low, go slow')","First-line for schizophrenia: any SGA (risperidone, aripiprazole, olanzapine, quetiapine, paliperidone, lurasidone) or FGA; selection guided by side effect profile and patient factors","For treatment-resistant schizophrenia (failed 2 adequate trials): clozapine is the ONLY antipsychotic with proven superiority; mandatory REMS enrollment with ANC monitoring","Manage EPS spectrum: benztropine/diphenhydramine for acute dystonia; propranolol/benzodiazepines for akathisia; dose reduction for parkinsonism; valbenazine/deutetrabenazine for tardive dyskinesia","Neuroleptic malignant syndrome: IMMEDIATE discontinuation of all antipsychotics, aggressive cooling, IV hydration, dantrolene (1-2.5 mg/kg IV) and/or bromocriptine (2.5-10 mg PO/NG TID)","Consider long-acting injectable antipsychotics (paliperidone palmitate, aripiprazole lauroxil, haloperidol decanoate) for adherence optimization in patients with history of non-adherence"],
    nursingActions: ["Perform comprehensive mental status examination: assess for hallucinations, delusions, thought disorganization, flat affect, and suicidal ideation before and during treatment","Monitor for neuroleptic malignant syndrome: check temperature, assess muscle rigidity, monitor mental status changes, and report autonomic instability (tachycardia, diaphoresis, labile BP) immediately","Assess for EPS at each encounter: observe for tremor, rigidity, abnormal gait, restlessness (akathisia), and involuntary movements (tardive dyskinesia)","For clozapine patients: verify ANC results before dispensing each supply; educate about signs of infection (fever, sore throat, flu-like symptoms requiring immediate blood draw)","Educate patients that antipsychotics require consistent adherence for efficacy; missed doses should not be doubled; discuss LAI options for adherence challenges","Monitor for sedation and fall risk, especially during initiation and dose titration; implement fall precautions and educate about avoiding driving until response is known"],
