    pearls: ["The four dopamine pathways are the conceptual framework for understanding antipsychotic effects: mesolimbic (positive symptoms), mesocortical (negative/cognitive symptoms), nigrostriatal (EPS), tuberoinfundibular (prolactin)—all antipsychotic side effects map to D2 blockade in specific pathways","EPS severity follows a temporal pattern: acute dystonia (hours to days) → akathisia (days to weeks) → drug-induced parkinsonism (weeks to months) → tardive dyskinesia (months to years); earlier effects are more reversible, tardive dyskinesia may be permanent","Neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS) is a psychiatric emergency: fever + rigidity + AMS + autonomic instability + CK elevation; mortality is 5-20%; treatment is immediate antipsychotic discontinuation + dantrolene + bromocriptine + aggressive supportive care","Clozapine is severely underutilized: despite being the only antipsychotic with proven superiority in treatment-resistant schizophrenia, it is prescribed to <5% of eligible patients due to monitoring burden and fear of agranulocytosis; advocate for appropriate referral","The difference between FGA and SGA mechanism: FGAs block D2 across all pathways non-selectively; SGAs add 5-HT2A blockade which disinhibits dopamine in nigrostriatal (reducing EPS) and mesocortical (potentially improving negative symptoms) pathways while maintaining mesolimbic D2 blockade","Tardive dyskinesia now has FDA-approved treatments: valbenazine (Ingrezza) and deutetrabenazine (Austedo)—both are VMAT2 inhibitors that reduce dopamine packaging into synaptic vesicles; assess with AIMS regularly and intervene early"],
